Japan consumes a quarter of the world's tuna, facing pressure from environmentalists due to overfishing.
An international commission reduced the Mediterranean bluefin tuna catch, leading to import shortages.
The Tokyo-based Organisation for Responsible Tuna Fisheries and Seoul's World Tuna Purse Seine Organisation called for a moratorium on large tuna vessels.
A joint statement expressed concerns about tuna stock depletion.
The meeting in Kobe aims to save tuna from extinction by sharing information and controlling illegal fishing.
Japan seeks sustainable tuna management, with global efforts to certify tuna origin and combat overfishing.
